{
"@context": [
"http://www.w3.org/ns/odrl.jsonld",
{
"ex": "https://hospital-example.org/",
"dbo": "http://dbpedia.org/ontology/",
"vcard": "http://www.w3.org/2006/vcard/ns#",
"ex:financialStatus": { "@type": "xsd:string" }
}
],
"@type": "odrl:Set",
"uid": "ex:policy/P09",
"prohibition": [{
"@type": "odrl:Prohibition",
"assigner": {
"@type": ["odrl:Party", "dbo:Hospital"],
"uid": "ex:authority",
"vcard:fn": "Hospital"
},
"assignee": {
"@type": ["odrl:PartyCollection", "vcard:Group"],
"uid": "ex:groups/admin-staff"
},
"action": "odrl:modify",
"target": "ex:systems/db/tables/Citas",
"constraint": [{
"@type": "odrl:Constraint",
"leftOperand": "ex:financialStatus",
"operator": "odrl:eq",
"rightOperand": "DEUDOR"
}]
}]
}
Design Observation (Limitation): Currently, the policy evaluates the action on the
Citas table, but the debt condition depends on the Facturación table. In a real-world
implementation, the evaluator requires a subquery to link the patient with their financial
status, which is a limitation in this flat JSON-LD model.
